title: Ukraine Plans Blackouts as It Braces for Extended Loss of Power
description: With an electricity grid heavily damaged by Russian missiles, emergency workers in Kyiv are considering a total blackout that would require the evacuation of three million residents.
dc:creator: The New York Times
media:credit: Finbarr O'Reilly for The New York Times
media:description: A Ukrainian tank returning from the front line near the town of Borova in the northeastern Kharkiv region on Friday.
